Patch Set 4:

The API is returning 500 response codes to requests that should give 204's because the add_to_backend() method isn't expecting the verifier kwarg.

Any idea why this is occurring? You've put the Depends-On tag on this patch and linked it to the patch adding the verifier kwarg to the backends so I don't know why this failing? Perhaps you need to rebase?

Patch Set 4:

The "Depends-On" prevents this patch from merging until the glance_store patch has merged, but I think the tests will fail until there is an official release of glance_store which includes the updates.  Since glance_store is a library that is installed based on requirements.txt, the "Depends-On" doesn't affect the version of glance_store used.

There might be a way to temporarily set the "requirements.txt" file so that the "Depends-On" version of the glance_store library is used instead (something like "-e git+https://github.com/openstack/glance_store.git#egg=glance_store") but I haven't been able to figure out what that should be.

IMO this should be marked as WIP until the ECC and DSA support get merged in Glance. If this merges before those do, then we could end up with a situation where valid ECC/DSA signatures that the user wants Nova to validate get flunked by Glance.

Patch Set 10:

@dane: The ECC and DSA patches are configured as dependent on this patch.  Since a new approach is being used (sign-the-data instead of sign-the-hash) I don't think it makes sense to merge the ECC and DSA patches with the sign-the-hash approach, and then turn around and merge the ECC and DSA patches with the sign-the-data approach after this patch merges.  I think it's preferable to merge this patch first (which is now awaiting a release of the glance_store library).
